Microfibre
An amazing polyester and nylon fiber mix used to make fabric. The fiber is split many times smaller than a human strand of hair. 😳This gives the fabric the ability to absorb up to 7 to 8 times its weight of liquid. The fibers generate a static electric charge when moved across a surface that attracts dust and contains it rather than spreading it around or releasing it into the air like other common fabrics. 
You have every reason to go the microfibre way, here are a few reasons why:
1. They are effective in capturing microbes: studies have shown that microfibre is more effective in capturing germs than cotton.
2. They prevent cross contamination: because they are available in multiple colors, they are an indispensable tool in color coding to prevent cross contamination
3. Reduces chemical and water use: this helps you save up on cleaning products. many times only a damp microfiber cloth is enough to effectively clean up. #microfibre #microfibrecloth #hygiene #colorcoding #crosscontamination #smartcleaning #health #healthyhabits #excellence #sustainablecleaning #sustainability #cleaning #cleaningtips #savings #misshygienic #cleaningbusiness #innovation #germfree #germcontrol #lagos #lagosnigeria #lagosbusiness #nigeria #nigerianbusiness
